benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/renameKey - Update a bundle externalKey

covered: Valid Request: Happy path (TC01) and header variations (TC14) demonstrate successful updates with 204.
Non-Existing Resource: Tests for non-existent bundle (TC04) and system state with no bundles (TC15) cover 404 responses.
Authorization: Tests for missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header (TC02) and unauthorized access (TC12) cover auth errors (client errors).
Server Error Handling: System dependency unavailable (TC13) covers 503 responses.

Validation and Input Handling: Multiple scenarios validate inputs (malformed bundleId TC03, missing body TC06, malformed JSON TC07, missing externalKey TC08, empty externalKey TC11, externalKey length boundaries TC10, externalKey conflict TC05, missing/invalid payload cases TC06/TC07/TC08/TC11).
Edge Cases and Field Handling: Extra fields in body TC09, special characters TC19, trailing spaces TC20, and extra header TC21 are covered.
Edge-case/Performance: Large payload (TC16) and response-time under load (TC23) covered under performance/edge scenarios.
Regression/Backwards Compatibility: Regression test (TC18) and backward compatibility with legacy clients (TC22).
gaps: Partial Update: No explicit test enforcing rejection/allowance of partial updates when multiple fields could be present.
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or 429 responses.
Caching Behavior: No tests for ETag/Cache-Control headers.
Internal Server Error: No test simulating 500 Internal Server Error (only 503 covered).
Boundary tests: no explicit test for 256-character externalKey beyond the 255-character case.
recommendations: Add explicit Partial Update tests to validate allowed fields and behavior when extra fields are present.
Add rate limiting tests to verify throttling behavior (e.g., 429).
Add caching tests to validate ETag/Cache-Control semantics.
Add a test simulating 500 Internal Server Error to cover server-side failures.
Add boundary tests for 256-character externalKey to complement the 255-character test.
Strengthen concurrency tests with more realistic multi-user scenarios and conflicts, and expand coverage beyond a single bundle.
Ensure tests cover 401/403 responses with invalid tokens or missing auth tokens.
Improve coverage for backward compatibility with additional client variations.
Consider performance tests under sustained load beyond 500ms, and include additional  response-time thresholds.
Expand accessibility checks to include more screen-reader scenarios and keyboard navigation validation.
